<Base title="Custom OTI, WTI, BWY & BWR Controllers | INNO" description="Configure transformer OTI, WTI, BWY and BWR temperature controllers by range, contacts, output, capillary, mounting and remote monitoring requirements.">
  <section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">Project configuration support</p><h1>Custom OTI, WTI, BWY and BWR Temperature Controllers</h1><p>Convert a transformer temperature requirement into a controlled mechanical, electrical and monitoring configuration.</p></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="answer-block"><strong>Customization answer.</strong> A transformer temperature controller can be reviewed around its temperature range, contacts, remote output, power, capillary, bulb, thread, mounting and environmental requirements. Availability must be confirmed against the selected model family.</div><div class="grid two">
    <article class="card metric"><h2>Temperature Measurement and Scale</h2><p>Confirm whether the controller represents transformer top oil or simulated winding temperature, then specify range, scale and accuracy requirement.</p></article>
    <article class="card metric"><h2>Cooling, Alarm and Trip Contacts</h2><p>Define contact quantity, switching sequence, control voltage, relay duty and assignment to cooling, alarm or trip circuits.</p></article>
    <article class="card metric"><h2>Remote Monitoring Interfaces</h2><p>Specify Pt100, 4–20 mA, RS485 or a compatible remote display together with signal scale, supply and receiving equipment.</p></article>
    <article class="card metric"><h2>Transformer Mechanical Interface</h2><p>Confirm mounting, sensing bulb, pocket, thread, insertion depth, capillary length, cable entry and site environment.</p></article>
  </div></div></section>
  <section class="section tint"><article class="container prose">
    <h2>What Can Be Configured on an OTI or BWY Controller?</h2><p>Oil temperature controller projects typically define the top-oil scale, number of cooling or alarm contacts, remote output and sensing assembly. The bulb and thread must match the transformer thermometer pocket, while the capillary must reach the panel without tension, crushing or a tight bend.</p>
    <h2>What Must Be Defined for a WTI or BWR Controller?</h2><p>A winding temperature controller adds the load-current thermal simulation. In addition to range, contacts and output, confirm the CT secondary current, converter or compound-transmitter arrangement and required winding-to-oil temperature rise. These values belong to the transformer design and should not be copied from an unrelated installation.</p>
    <h2>OEM Review for New Transformer Production</h2><p>For a recurring production program, provide the transformer series, approved drawings, terminal philosophy, required model quantities and destination markets. A controlled selection sheet can standardize product codes and reduce variation between purchasing, assembly and commissioning records.</p>
    <h2>Replacement Review for Existing Transformers</h2><p>Send the complete existing model code, front and nameplate photographs, terminal diagram, scale, contact functions, output, mounting footprint, bulb, thread and capillary length. A similar family name does not prove drop-in compatibility. Any planned signal or wiring change should be identified before ordering.</p>
    <h3>Documents Confirmed Before an Order</h3><p>Request the current model-specific datasheet, outline drawing and terminal diagram. Confirm communication details, applicable quality documents and commercial terms for the final configuration. This website describes selection logic but does not imply that every possible option combination is a standard product.</p>
  </article></section>
  <EmailCTA title="Send an OTI, WTI, BWY or BWR Requirement" subject="Custom transformer temperature controller request" />
</Base>
